						               													<description>Bradley Raymond is one of the world's most successful horror writers. So, it only makes sense that he lives in Valley Falls where frightening things seem to lurk around every corner. Raymond is known for writing about things that go bump in the night and about monsters that wear human faces. Yet, when people begin to be murdered in ways that mimic the plots of some of his most famous novels, it becomes clear that someone is doing their best to frame him. Things take a turn for the worst when it is discovered that the most recent victim can be linked to one of his unpublished manuscripts. Is the killer a member of Bradley Raymond's inner circle? Did his novels inspire a murderer to commit these atrocities? Or is there more to Bradley Raymond than meets the eye? Do the Monster Mash and find out!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;As with all Deadbolt Mystery Society games, you step into the role of the detective. Examining the evidence provided, visiting different locations and using the password protected QR mechanic to uncover the truth.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players win once they catch the killer, find what's missing or whatever else is needed to solve the case at hand.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
